Overview
This issue defines the first version of the Deal Score Algorithm, the core intelligence behind the vehicle analysis engine.

The Deal Score determines whether a car listing is:

Good Deal

Fair Price

Overpriced

Potentially Risky

The algorithm must be deterministic, explainable, and data-driven.

AI will not determine the score — it will only explain the results to the user.

Goal
Provide users with a simple, trustworthy summary of a vehicle listing by combining:

market price signals

mileage adjustments

reliability risk

recall information

listing red flags

All factors will combine into a Deal Score (0–100).

Deal Score Breakdown
The score will be calculated using weighted components.

Factor | Weight | Purpose -- | -- | -- Price vs Market Value | 40% | Determine if the car is priced fairly Mileage Evaluation | 20% | Penalize excessive mileage Reliability Tier | 20% | Assess known issues and brand reliability Recall / Safety Issues | 10% | Penalize active recalls or safety problems Listing Risk Flags | 10% | Detect suspicious listings
AI Explanation Layer
Once the score is calculated, the AI system will:

explain why the score was assigned

highlight key positives

highlight risks

generate inspection checklist

suggest negotiation strategy

Example output:

"This vehicle is slightly under market value but has above-average mileage and known transmission issues. Consider negotiating 5–10% below the asking price."

🏗 Implementation Notes
The algorithm should be implemented as a server-side scoring engine.

Example endpoint:

POST /api/analyze-listing
Input:

{
  year,
  make,
  model,
  trim,
  mileage,
  price,
  location,
  vin
}
Output:

{
  deal_score,
  price_score,
  mileage_score,
  reliability_score,
  recall_score,
  risk_score,
  explanation
}
Future Improvements
Possible upgrades for later versions:

machine learning pricing models

regional market adjustments

real-time market comps

auction price signals

ownership cost predictions

Success Criteria
The algorithm should:

produce consistent results

be explainable

avoid AI hallucinations

provide clear user guidance

function with minimal input data